text: Pik Pobeda (or Peak Pobeda) is a mountain in the Tian Shan range, in Xinjiang and Kyrgyzstan. It is also known as Jengish Chokusu. Pik Pobeda is the highest mountain in Kyrgyzstan and the 60th highest mountain in the world. It should not be confused with a different mountain with the same name in Russia. The first people to reach the top were Vitali Abalakov and his team, in 1956. ==References== Category:Mountains of Kyrgyzstan Category:Mountains of Xinjiang
